TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bris, Arturo
AU  - Gulen, Huseyin
AU  - Kadiyala, Padma
AU  - Rau, P. Raghavendra
T1  - Good Stewards, Cheap Talkers, or Family Men? The Impact of Mutual Fund Closures on Fund Managers, Flows, Fees, and Performance
PY  - 2007
Y1  - 2007/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhl017
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 20
IS  - 3
SP  - 953
EP  - 982
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We examine a sample of 125 equity mutual funds that closed to new investment between 1993 and 2004. We find that funds close following a period of superior performance and abnormal fund inflows. Fund managers raise their fees when they close to compensate managers for losses in income due to the restrictions in size imposed by the fund closure decision. Managers reopen when fund size declines. However, they do not earn superior returns after reopening, suggesting that the fund closure decision does not provide information about superior fund managers. (JEL G14, G23)
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhl017
ER  - 



